Riot reportedly broke out in Katangan area of Warji Local Government Area of Bauchi State on Saturday as irate youths reportedly burnt houses and injured a pastor over another case of alleged blasphemy. DAILY POST gathered that the violence began when a message was allegedly circulated on social media that a Christian girl in the town allegedly engaged in blasphemy of Islam while reacting to the Sokoto incident. Details of the incident are still sketchy as the Stateâ€™s Police Public Relations Officer, Ahmed Wakili could not take his calls and was unable to reply text messages forwarded to him.